This paper proposes a new algorithm for autonomous learning agents in open-ended environments. The algorithm combines reinforcement learning, value function approximation, and automated curriculum learning mechanisms. The paper focuses on experiments conducted in a modular-goal robotic environment, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV).
